                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <p>Fol. <locus target="#00v"/>: ነ፡ሰላ፡ግዕ፡ብፁአን፡ነቢያት፡አላ፡በተአምኖ፡ተጋደሉ፡ፈድፋደ፡ጸንዑ፡እምቀደምቶሙ፡...</p>
                           
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding contemporary="true">
                        <decoNote xml:id="b1">
                           <p>The manuscript has no boards. The quires are sewn on two pairs of sewing stations.  They were probably meant for at least two different manuscripts (quires I, II, III still have “tackets”) and were unified by chance. Quire V (fols. <locus from="35" to="39"/>) is made of heterogeneous, crudely manufactured parchment leaves (only fol. <locus target="#37"/>is ruled).  </p>
                           
                        </decoNote>
                     </binding>
                  </bindingDesc>
